# SYS-LIC-GATE-Z1
## License Validation Controller

Version: 2.0

---

# Overview

SYS-LIC-GATE-Z1 serves as the authorization boundary for the HyperSync License Operating System.

Every provisioning request must pass through this controller before any downstream execution is permitted.

Unlike traditional workflow validation that relies on isolated business rules, Gate Z1 performs deterministic operational authorization by evaluating license state, governance status, execution capacity, and processing integrity before issuing an execution decision.

The controller functions as the authoritative authorization layer for the entire License Operating System.

---

# Architectural Purpose

Gate Z1 is responsible for:

• License Authorization

• Execution Eligibility Validation

• Operational State Verification

• Governance Enforcement

• Execution Capacity Validation

• Authorization Decision Generation

• Immutable Audit Generation

---

# Core Responsibilities

The controller performs a comprehensive validation of operational readiness including:

- License Status
- Tier Status
- Stage Status
- Processing Lock
- Authorization Status
- Webhook Registration
- Execution Capacity
- Correlation Integrity
- Requested Zap Validation
- License Identity Validation

Only requests satisfying every operational requirement are authorized.

